org.springframework.cloud.dataflow.core.dsl

Class TaskVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.cloud.dataflow.core.dsl.TaskVisitor
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GraphGeneratorVisitor, TaskValidatorVisitor

    public abstract class TaskVisitor
extends Object
    Basic visitor pattern for a parsed task. Provide a concrete implementation to participate in the visit and pass it to a parsed TaskNode. A simple task only has one sequence, for example: appA && appB && appC. In this situation preVisit(int) and postVisit(int) will only be called with 0. A more complex situation would be: 
     
 appA && appB 0->:foo *->appC
 foo: appD && appE
    This includes two sequences - as in two separate definitions. The primary definition references other definitions where it would be too messy to inline them. In this case preVisit(int) would be called for both 0 and 1.
    Author:
    Andy Clement

      • preVisit

        public boolean preVisit(TaskAppNode taskApp)
        This preVisit/visit/postVisit sequence for taskApp is not invoked for inlined references to apps in transitions, for example: appA 0->:foo 1->appB. The reference to appB would be seen in the transition visit below.
        Parameters:
        taskApp - the use of a task app in a task dsl
        Returns:
        false to skip visiting this taskApp
